    <ul style=" color:White; text-align:left">
    <li><h3 class="style8">ROBOT SPECIFICATION:</h3>
        <ul>
        <li class="style7">Robot should be manually controlled.</li>
        <li class="style7">Robot can be wired or wireless. Wireless robots should have at least two modes of frequency to avoid frequency interference.</li>
        <li class="style7">The robot must fit into a box of dimension: 30cm x 30cm x 45cm.</li>
        <li class="style7">Weight of robot must not exceed 4kg.</li>
        <li class="style7">Dimensions may exceed after the beginning of event.</li>
        <li class="style7">The dimension of robot defined above is excluding reloading mechanism.</li>
        <li class="style7">Lego kits and complete car bases are not allowed.</li></ul>
    </li>
    <li><h3 class="style8">POWER SUPPLY:</h3>
        <ul>
        <li class="style7">The potential difference between any two points of the robot should not exceed 24V.</li>
        <li class="style7">A fixed 220V, 50Hz power supply will be provided by the organizers. Participants may choose to use their own power sources.</li>
        <li class="style7">Organizers are not responsible for any power fluctuations.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><h3 class="style8">GENERAL RULES:</h3>
        <ul>
        <li class="style7">The team can have a maximum of 3 members, not necessarily of the same institute.</li>
        <li class="style7">The name of the machine must be prominently displayed.</li>
        <li class="style7">The machine will be checked for its safety before the race and will be discarded if found unsafe for other participants and spectators.</li>
        <li class="style7">One team-member will control the robot from a pre decided remote location. </li>
        <li><span class="style7">The team will be disqualified if:
            </span>
            <ol type="1"><li class="style7">The robot damages the arena in any way. </li>
                <li class="style7"> If any team is found using any unfair means.</li>
                <li class="style7">It is not ready at the time specified.</li>
            </ol>
        </li>
        <li class="style7">No part of the robot, intentionally or unintentionally, should be left in the arena after the maximum allotted time. In such cases penalty will be awarded.</li>
        <li class="style7">The organizers reserve the rights to change any or all of the rules as they deem fit. Change in rules, if any will be highlighted on the website and notified to the registered participants.</li>
        <li class="style7">Judges decision shall be treated as final and binding on all.</li></ul></li>
    </ul>
